<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Perennial herb with tap root and stems somewhat woody below, similar in all details to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 153. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scammonia" order="Solanales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scammonia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Convolvulus scammonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but stems erect to 60 cm, leaves 1.5-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.8 cm, sagittate, the central lobe narrowly oblong-lanceolate, basal auricles small, simple. The peduncles appear always to bear only 1-2 flowers and the bracteoles are filiform, not more than 0.5 mm wide. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 242; 
<bibRefCitation author="Parris, BS" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Turkey" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="198 - 219" refId="B256" refString="Parris, BS, 1978. Convolvulus. Flora of Turkey volume 6: 198 - 219" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 6" year="1978">Parris 1978</bibRefCitation>
: 218]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
